definition.value: A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of avicholic acid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that is the dizwitterionic form of L-lanthionine obtained by migration of protons from both carboxy groups to the amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that is the dizwitterionic form of L-homolanthionine obtained by migration of protons from both carboxy groups to the amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid aldehyde that is any steroid which is substituted by a formyl group at position 14.

A member of the class of indoles that is 1H-indole substituted by 4-chlorobenzyl and formyl groups at positions 1 and 3, respectively. It is an anti-cancer agent that is active against lung cancer cells with K-Ras mutations.
